MATOLA – Twenty-five protesters were arrested on the N4 near Matola in Mozambique on Wednesday afternoon. According to Gerhard Coetzer from Securicon, the police are dispersing and arresting anyone without a good reason to be there.  Traffic was disrupted in Machanchuene, located on the N4 just outside. After four hours the whole situation was resolved and the road was back to normal.  ALSO READ: 62 year-old victim of Alkmaar attack tells her story